02/06/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Police arrested on Tuesday (June 1st) three inspectors suspected of corruption worth 100,000 euros.
The men were caught while allegedly demanding a 16,000-euro bribe from a businessman to complete the customs procedure for some cargo.
Police say the inspectors required a 10,000-euro "fee" for every cargo ship entering the port of Vlora.
(Top Channel, Lajmifundit, Balkan Web, Shekulli - 02/06/10)
